# Initial release of the Erlang code generator for Idris 2

Read the [announcement at elixirforum.com](https://elixirforum.com/t/erlang-code-generator-for-idris-2/34630).

The Erlang code generator for Idris 2 is available on [GitHub](https://github.com/chrrasmussen/Idris2-Erlang).

The following packages are now available on [Hex](https://hex.pm):
- [idris2](https://github.com/chrrasmussen/Idris2-Erlang) — The Idris 2 compiler running on the Erlang VM [[Hex](https://hex.pm/packages/idris2)]
- [mix_idris2](https://github.com/chrrasmussen/mix_idris2) — Mix compiler to help compile Idris 2 code in Elixir projects [[Hex](https://hex.pm/packages/mix_idris2)]

A big thank you to:
- [@yurrriq](https://github.com/yurrriq) — For adding support for building the Erlang code generator via Nix, and for adding a Nix workflow!
- [@tipsy](https://github.com/tipsy) — For making the logo for this website, for improving the design, and making the website mobile friendly!
